text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:45:21.643000','2025-06-01 02:45:21.643000',NULL,8,8,'zh-CN'),(17,'ng17d528b9x7vuzwmzde62fz','合约编号C84-0032 星光大道活化工程 – 供应﹑组装﹑测试和校验甲板拆卸和重建合约','合约编号C84-0032 星光大道活化工程 – 供应﹑组装﹑测试和校验甲板拆卸和重建合约','新世界发展有限公司','2015 年 12 月 17 日 - 2018 年 09 月 16 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道活化计划于2015年8月宣布推行，并于2019年重开。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道甲板重建是整个星光大道活化计划的其中一个工程合约，工程主要包括拆卸和重建星光大道原有的甲板结构，修复十字头以及组装预制的覆盖层。施工范围同时包括拆卸和重建连接星光大道和香港洲际酒店的行人天桥。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道活化计划自推出以来一直广受大众传媒的关注。工期时间短是项目团队面对的主要挑战 – 长400米的混凝土桥梁结构需在短短11个月内完成拆卸和重建，而工程需于海洋环境进行亦大大增加了施工难度。工程最后以顺利完成实有赖工程团队优秀的项目管理，并在公共关系﹑品质管理﹑项目监控﹑预算控制﹑安全和环境等各方面的达至高水平。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:45:21.643000','2025-06-01 02:45:21.643000','2025-06-01 02:45:21.693000',8,8,'zh-CN'),(18,'ylt03z8kym9rg0k8a14fgoq2','合約編號C84-0032 星光大道活化工程 – 供應﹑組裝﹑測試和校驗甲板拆卸和重建合約','合約編號C84-0032 星光大道活化工程 – 供應﹑組裝﹑測試和校驗甲板拆卸和重建合約','新世界發展有限公司','2015 年 12 月 17 日 - 2018 年 09 月 16 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道活化計劃於2015年8月宣布推行，並於2019年重開。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道甲板重建是整個星光大道活化計劃的其中一個工程合約，工程主要包括拆卸和重建星光大道原有的甲板結構，修復十字頭以及組裝預製的覆蓋層。施工範圍同時包括拆卸和重建連接星光大道和香港洲際酒店的行人天橋。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"星光大道活化計劃自推出以來一直廣受大眾傳媒的關注。工期時間短是項目團隊面對的主要挑戰 – 長400米的混凝土橋樑結構需在短短11個月內完成拆卸和重建，而工程需於海洋環境進行亦大大增加了施工難度。工程最後以順利完成實有賴工程團隊優秀的項目管理，並在公共關係﹑品質管理﹑項目監控﹑預算控制﹑安全和環境等各方面的達至高水平。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:46:54.136000','2025-06-15 03:36:32.896000',NULL,8,8,'zh-Hant-HK'),(20,'b50cndfrvokkonli5c3l4f6n','Package Contract No. C84-0032 AOS Revitalization - Supply, Installation, Testing and Commissioning of Demolition and Re-Construction of Decking Package Contract','Package Contract No. C84-0032 AOS Revitalization - Supply, Installation, Testing and Commissioning of Demolition and Re-Construction of Decking Package Contract','New World Construction Company Limited','17 December 2015 - 16 September 2018','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The revitalization plan of Avenue of Stars (AOS) was announced in 2015 and the avenue was reopened in 2019.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The reconstruction of the deck structure along the avenue was one of the package contracts of the AOS revitalization project. The works include the demolition and reconstruction of the existing AOS deck structure, the reparation of existing crossheads and the installation of precast cladding panels. It also involves the demolition and reconstruction of the existing connecting bridge from AOS to Hotel InterContinental Hong Kong.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The AOS project was carried out under the spot lights of mass media. The major challenge facing by the project team is the short contract period. With an ambitious project timeframe, the demolition and reconstruction of around 400m long concrete bridge structure in marine condition is completed within 11 months. The project team is proud to successfully complete the project with high standard of project management in terms of public relation, quality assurance, programme monitoring, budget control, safety and environmental.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:48:39.570000','2025-06-06 08:21:51.229000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(22,'hbinfc3pmw9x3iosp9jvrqe2','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','New World Construction Company Limited','17 December 2013 - 17 March 2016','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The demolition and reconstruction works of New World Centre commenced in January 2009. In line with its business development plan, Sea Deck with an area of about 18 meters by 94 meters werel also reconstructed.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project is divided into two phases: the first phase involved the demolition and alteration of existing sea deck (Area A to C), and the reconstruction of reinforced concrete sea deck (Area A to C). Apart from demolishing and reconstructing the remaining sea deck, the second phase also requires the construction of a bored pile of 800 mm in diameter inside the existing two-metre caissons. Crossing the two phases of the project also was the fabrication and installation of precast concrete intake channel about 30 metres long by 2.5 metres high and 5.6 to 10 metres wide.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Although the site was near the sea, subject to the \\\"Avenue of Stars\\\" in the south, marine works machinery could not be used because of the lack of access. Instead only onshore cranes and construction of temporary platforms when could be relied on considering the construction plan. Due to the Protection of the Harbour Ordinance, extension of the temporary platforms in existing structure and lifting method were used instead of seabed-based supporting methods.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"As the site was very close to the hotel and tourist area, apart from increasing resources to reduce the noise, we also had to implement the demolition works within a limited time according to the hotel\'s requirements so as to maintain the normal operation of the hotel. However, due to the limited available work space and the need to coordinate with other site works, resources could not be increased simply at any time to catch up with the progress. Therefore, project team had to find alternative ways to shorten the construction time at each stage of the construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:50:10.148000','2025-06-01 02:50:10.148000',NULL,8,8,'en'),(23,'hbinfc3pmw9x3iosp9jvrqe2','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','New World Construction Company Limited','17 December 2013 - 17 March 2016','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The demolition and reconstruction works of New World Centre commenced in January 2009. In line with its business development plan, Sea Deck with an area of about 18 meters by 94 meters werel also reconstructed.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project is divided into two phases: the first phase involved the demolition and alteration of existing sea deck (Area A to C), and the reconstruction of reinforced concrete sea deck (Area A to C). Apart from demolishing and reconstructing the remaining sea deck, the second phase also requires the construction of a bored pile of 800 mm in diameter inside the existing two-metre caissons. Crossing the two phases of the project also was the fabrication and installation of precast concrete intake channel about 30 metres long by 2.5 metres high and 5.6 to 10 metres wide.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Although the site was near the sea, subject to the \\\"Avenue of Stars\\\" in the south, marine works machinery could not be used because of the lack of access. Instead only onshore cranes and construction of temporary platforms when could be relied on considering the construction plan. Due to the Protection of the Harbour Ordinance, extension of the temporary platforms in existing structure and lifting method were used instead of seabed-based supporting methods.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"As the site was very close to the hotel and tourist area, apart from increasing resources to reduce the noise, we also had to implement the demolition works within a limited time according to the hotel\'s requirements so as to maintain the normal operation of the hotel. However, due to the limited available work space and the need to coordinate with other site works, resources could not be increased simply at any time to catch up with the progress. Therefore, project team had to find alternative ways to shorten the construction time at each stage of the construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:50:10.148000','2025-06-01 02:50:10.148000','2025-06-01 02:50:10.183000',8,8,'en'),(24,'sgqwo0gf6iflgmp5zim5lawv','新世界中心重建-海上露天平台改建和加建工程','新世界中心重建-海上露天平台改建和加建工程','新世界建筑有限公司','2013 年 12 月 17 日 - 2016 年 03 月 17 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"为配合业务发展，新世界中心于二零零九年一月开始进行拆卸及重建工程。当中面积约十八米乘九四米的海上露天平台亦会改建及加建。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"工程分为两期：第一期将特定范围的海上露天平台结构拆卸，再重建组合式横樑及钢筋溷凝土楼面。第二期除了拆除剩下海上露天平台拆卸及重建外，亦需要在现有两米海桩内打造一条直径800mm的鑽孔灌注桩。当中亦包括新造一段约30米长，2.5米高5.6至10米阔的海水进水管槽，此工作将横跨一二期工程。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"工地虽然临海，但受制于南面的\\\"星光大道\\\"，海事工程机械因没有通道而不能被採用，在考虑施工方案时只能依靠岸上吊机及建造临时台。亦因要配合保护海港条例，大部份以海床为基础的承托方法都不能应用，需要尽量应用现有结构伸延临时台或以吊重方式施工。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"由于工地极接近酒店及游客区，除了增加资源于减噪设施外，我们亦要因应酒店的要求，在限定时间内进行打拆的工序，以维持酒店正常运作。但亦受制于有限的可用工作空间及须配合场内其他工程，以致不能随时以增加资源来追赶进度。工程团队苦煞思量地不断研究各工序的关係，寻求替代方法缩短施工时间。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:51:19.512000','2025-06-01 02:51:19.512000',NULL,8,8,'zh-CN'),(25,'sgqwo0gf6iflgmp5zim5lawv','新世界中心重建-海上露天平台改建和加建工程','新世界中心重建-海上露天平台改建和加建工程','新世界建筑有限公司','2013 年 12 月 17 日 - 2016 年 03 月 17 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"为配合业务发展，新世界中心于二零零九年一月开始进行拆卸及重建工程。当中面积约十八米乘九四米的海上露天平台亦会改建及加建。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"工程分为两期：第一期将特定范围的海上露天平台结构拆卸，再重建组合式横樑及钢筋溷凝土楼面。第二期除了拆除剩下海上露天平台拆卸及重建外，亦需要在现有两米海桩内打造一条直径800mm的鑽孔灌注桩。当中亦包括新造一段约30米长，2.5