partment','20 January 2011 - 15 July 2013','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The main purpose of the Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"One of the contracts of Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. As the tunnel must straddle the existing MTR Tsuen Wan Line, major constraint was anticipated during the construction. Since the span-over structure is a heavy massive box, an off-site pre-fabrication method was adopted to avoid imposing loading on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. The completed box structure was towed to site by sea for final installation. This construction method proved to be more cost effective and did not cause any impact on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line during the construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:11:20.228000','2025-06-01 03:11:20.228000',NULL,8,8,'en'),(45,'pog1o3rd5ksspse7npb3r5y1','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line (Contract No. HK/2010/06)','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line','Civil Engineering and Development Department','20 January 2011 - 15 July 2013','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The main purpose of the Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"One of the contracts of Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. As the tunnel must straddle the existing MTR Tsuen Wan Line, major constraint was anticipated during the construction. Since the span-over structure is a heavy massive box, an off-site pre-fabrication method was adopted to avoid imposing loading on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. The completed box structure was towed to site by sea for final installation. This construction method proved to be more cost effective and did not cause any impact on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line during the construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:11:20.228000','2025-06-01 03:11:20.228000','2025-06-01 03:11:20.273000',8,8,'en'),(46,'ko7fxymfizjsf48195ae1mde','Presidential Palace Project, Abu Dhabi UAE (Marine Package - MA1)','Presidential Palace Project, Abu Dhabi UAE','Ministry of Presidential Affairs','06 September 2010 - 05 September 2011','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project involves carrying out enabling works in the North West of Emirates Palace Hotel (EPH). It includes preparing the North Shore for construction of a reinforced concrete sea wall of approximately 1,650m long, creation of rock groynes for tidal / erosion control, removal of existing rock groynes, fabrication and installation of decorative reinforced precast concrete (GRC) cladding panels to the face of the sea wall, and construction of reinforced concrete wave deflector beam, steps, flower beds/planter boxes and other wall components.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:13:00.347000','2025-06-01 03:13:00.347000',NULL,8,8,'en'),(47,'ko7fxymfizjsf48195ae1mde','Presidential Palace Project, Abu Dhabi UAE (Marine Package - MA1)','Presidential Palace Project, Abu Dhabi UAE','Ministry of Presidential Affairs','06 September 2