 2.5m through the existing hillside north of the power station to Yung Shue Wan South Landing Point; and\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Design and construction, instrumentation and completion of the horse-shoe shape cable tunnels of approximately 130m in length having an internal clear nominal diameter of 2.5m through the existing hillside from Pak Kok San Tsuen to Pak Kok Tsui.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:47:06.744000','2025-06-06 08:17:32.890000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(137,'gmjtohgrj1fczrkng21vydoj',' Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan (Contract No. ST 97/03)','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:48:59.655000','2025-06-06 08:19:20.910000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(139,'bp5u6ncod6z12l039nzd7le5','Construction of Lung Kwu Chau Jetty (Contract No. CV/2002/11)','Construction of Lung Kwu Chau Jetty','Civil Engineering Department','04 April 2003 - 20 November 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of a precast concrete blockwork jetty (10m by 20m) with a single berth; construction of a concrete catwalk (approximately 22m long); dredging of an approach channel up to 2.5m deep in front of the berth; extension of the existing footpath connecting to the proposed jetty; supply and installation / construction of the associated marine facilities and demolition of the existing jetty upon completion of the proposed jetty.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:50:40.518000','2025-06-06 08:20:21.490000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(141,'t3mk016ovj36cs22gvo4kmy7','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Quarry Bay and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo (Contract No. CV/2001/02)','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Quarry Bay and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo','Civil Engineering Department','05 December 2001 - 07 July 2005','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the modification and management of the Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun & Quarry Bay; management of the Public Filling storage area at Mui Wo and landscaping works within the Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:51:47.754000','2025-06-06 08:22:56.427000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(143,'y5knm2adunrwcbyf4rl0s3d6','Reconstruction of Pak Sha Wan Public Pier in Sai Kung and Reconstruction of Dolphins in Shau Kei Wan Typhoon Shelter (Contract No. CV/99/13)','Reconstruction of Pak Sha Wan Public Pier in Sai Kung and Reconstruction of Dolphins in Shau Kei Wan Typhoon Shelter','Civil Engineering Department','01 February 2000 - 31 January 2002','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project is to construct a new public pier in Pak Sha Wan of Sai Kung and to demolish the existing public pier after commissioning of the new public pier.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major challenge of the project is the piling work for the pier deck structure. To overcome problems associated with complex sub-soil condition and to minimize impact to an environmental sensitive area, pre-bored socketted H-pile with permanent steel casing was used to replace the conventional driven pile system. The alternative piling system was successfully completed within the given time frame while substantially reducing impact to the surrounding environment.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Another special feature of the project is to maintain operation of the public pier during construction of the new pier and  demolition of the existing pier. Construction method and sequence were carefully planned to minimize nuisance to public. This includes the provision of temporary covered walkway for pier users, pre-fabrication of the pier and superstructure elements off-site as far as possible to shorten on-site construction time, and demolition of the existing pier by saw cutting method to minimize environmental impacts.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Site was awarded a \\\"Considerate Contractor Site Award\\\" by the Public Works Bureau in consideration of good site management, being considerate to nearby residents and passerbys, environmental consciousness, safety consciousness and law abiding.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:52:49.826000','2025-06-06 08:23:07.692000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(145,'zt5iq78cj30grbu3lqcwdxji','Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay (Contract No. CV/98/14)','Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay','Civil Engineering Department','02 August 1999 - 31 December 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes setting up and management of a Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay and carrying out environmental monitoring and implementation of environmental mitigation measures.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:53:58.786000','2025-06-06 08:22:33.697000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(147,'sebrngz255j42ad9itm2qhlk','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo (Contract No. CV/98/15)','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo','Civil Engineering Department','30 July 1999 - 31 December 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the setting up and management of a Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun; carrying out of environmental monitoring and implementation of environmental mitigation measures for Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun; landscape works within Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and management of a Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:55:01.852000','2025-06-06 08:22:45.309000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(149,'vfb0y556v65526ki0tg3wbm3','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Works involved:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}]','2025-06-01 05:57:33.411000','2025-06-06 08:22:08.949000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(151,'iyzlq59nougs5ubraqh8kl2r','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun (TMTL 393)','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works. \", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:59:32.879000','2025-06-06 08:23:38.022000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(153,'uar1s6syc8qnla2u0qv7wiqy',' Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains (Contract No. CV/94/06)','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Port Works Division / Civil Engineering Department','01 September 1995 - 31 January 2000','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes the construction of 450m long vertical seawall, 1000m long sloping rubble seawall, 625m long 4-cells drainage culvert, roads, sewers, drains and watermains and reclamation of 28 hectares of land.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 06:00:41.492000','2025-06-06 08:20:09.880000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(155,'pplrhxdmbg1yerlaf9ds53oj',' 沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山 (合约编号：ST 97-03)','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山','拓展署','2004 年 03 月 26 日 - 2006 年 11 月 18 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"项目包括沙田及马鞍山区内土木工程项目并特别针对于斜坡，道路及渠务工程。由于涉及交通不便的地区，我们采用了崭新的施工方法。 如在多石村后山山上建造一条120米长围栏，我们利用了直升机运送围栏组件到现场及使用特殊设计滑轮系统利用人力安装整个围栏。在修葺2公里长马鞍山海滨长廊时，我们利用陆地及海上机械设备来运输及放置防波堤石。避免对邻近海堤附近的居民做成滋扰，我们在施工过程中应用不同环境的预防措施及与市民建立良好的沟通系统。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 06:02:24.896000','2025-06-01 06:02:24.896000',NULL,8,8,'zh-CN'),(156,'pplrhxdmbg1yerlaf9ds53oj',' 沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山 (合约编号：ST 97-03)','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山','拓展署','2004 年 03 月 26 日 - 2006 年 11 月 18 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"项目包括沙田及马鞍山区内土木工程项目并特别针对于斜坡，道路及渠务工程。由于涉及交通不便的地区，我们采用了崭新的施工方法。 如在多石村后山山上建造一条120米长围栏，我们利用了直升机运送围栏组件到现场及使用特殊设计滑轮系统利用人力安装整个围栏。在修葺2公里长马鞍山海滨长廊时，我们利用陆地及海上机械设备来运输及放置防波堤石。避免对邻近海堤附近的居民做成滋扰，我们在施工过程中应用不同环境的预防措施及与市民建立良好的沟通系统。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 06:02:24.896000','2025-06-01 06:02:24.896000','2025-06-01 06:02:24.940000',8,8,'zh-CN'),(157,'fk503slx0pja0m7tr8lx3vo4','建造龙鼓州码头 (合约编号： CV/2002/11)'