ase I','Civil Engineering Department','01 April 1991 - 31 August 1993','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes dredging of 34 million m3 of marine mud, formation of 75 ha of reclaimed land using marine sand,  construction of a public cargo working area, seawall, underground pump houses and associated road and drainage works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project brought together a formidable fleet of dredgers, including trailing suction hopper, cutter suction and large grab dredgers.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"A total of 9,700 concrete blocks, each weighing about 20 tonnes, were made by the company at its precasting yard in Tsuen Wan and shipped in by Derrick Lighter for construction of the vertical seawall.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"As Hong Kong is one of the busiest ports in the world, the crewmen on board the dredgers had to be especially vigilant to avoid the constant flow of ships, both day and night.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:49:42.798000','2025-06-06 08:17:46.854000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(225,'h5zfqnwarn9khb9go6l5sq05','Stanley Area Sewerage and Sewage Disposal Submarine Outfall (Contract No. CV/89/32)','Stanley Area Sewerage and Sewage Disposal Submarine Outfall','Drainage Services Department','01 February 1991 - 31 July 1992','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of a 610m diameter, 2.3km long submarine outfall pipeline to a point in Sheung Sze Mun; construction of a 610mm diameter, 210m long overflow pipeline parallel to the outfall; construction of a valve chamber and installation of a cathodic protection system.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:51:01.112000','2025-06-06 08:24:20.404000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(227,'ndjlop6r320xknpxlli6d0fw','Penny\'s Bay Power Station, Lantau Island','Penny\'s Bay Power Station, Lantau Island','China Light & Power Company Limited','01 August 1990 - 30 April 1992','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project had an extremely tight schedule. All site formation and general civil works, from the set up at the first landing point in a small remote bay of Lantau Island, had to be completed within 20 months to allow for the subsequent installation of three sets of gas turbine generators and associated facilities. Safety and environmental mitigation measures during the construction works were also the main area of concern. The construction programme was well planned so that various types of plant equipment and manpower resources could be mobilized on site at different stages of the construction to maximize the efficiency and progress of the project. The right plants together with the right personnel was also key to success of the project.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:51:57.827000','2025-06-06 08:22:21.564000',NULL,8,3,'en'),(229,'ujjq3ndsqjeku9zsyi13gewm',' Civil Works for 275 KV Cable Route from Lamma Island to Cyberport (Contract No. 03/8013)','Civil Works for 275 KV Cable Route from Lamma Island to Cyberport','The Hong Kong Electric Co., Ltd.','25 May 2004 - 14 June 2007','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of landing points at Yung Shue Wan South, Pak Kok Tsui, Pak Kok San Tsuen and Cyberport including all excavation, installation of silt curtain, temporary supporting, drainage provisions, back filling, RC cable joint bay construction, dredging, marine works, seawall construction, rock fill, cable slop way , slope formation, submarine cable markers and reinstating works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Design and construction, instrumentation and completion of the horse-shoe shaped cable tunnels of approximately 220m in length ha