 ships, both day and night.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:49:42.798000','2025-06-06 08:17:46.854000','2025-06-06 08:17:46.921000',8,3,'en'),(231,'wrf26qjeq8i2qpl7sgerwwtc',' Contract No. DC/2009/13 Construction of Sewage Treatment Works at Yung Shue Wan and Sok Kwu Wan','Contract No. DC/2009/13 Construction of Sewage Treatment Works at Yung Shue Wan and Sok Kwu Wan','Drainage Services Department','17 May 2010 - 22 December 2015','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"A sewage treatment at Yung Shue Wan on Lamma Island with a capacity of 2,850m3/day (ADWF) to provide secondary treatment with degritting, screening, grease removal and nutrient removal is to be constructed. This project involves civil, E&M works and all other ancillary building services, architectural, landscape and establishment works; construction of a submarine outfall of approximately 500m long at Yung Shue Wan of which a minimum 400m of submarine outfall from the coastline shall be constructed by Horizontal Directional Drilling.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major works of this project also include construction of a sewage treatment works at Sok Kwu Wan on Lamma Island, involving civil, E&M works and all other ancillary building services, architectural, landscape and establishment works and approximately 600m rising main from Sok Kwu Wan Sewage Treatment Works to the outfall chamber; construction of a submarine outfall of approximately 750m long at Sok Kwu Wan of which a minimum 650m of submarine outfall from the coastline shall be constructed by Horizontal Directional Drilling.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project is the first time Horizontal Directional Drilling has been adopted in Hong Kong. It offers significant environmental advantages over traditional cut and cover pipeline/utility installations.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:22:12.976000','2025-06-06 08:17:57.465000','2025-06-06 08:17:57.532000',8,3,'en'),(232,'mrqk4wmzgzpmwhfwruonx2dw',' Fishing Harbour in Baaya-Sila Rock Placing and Underwater Excavation','Fishing Harbour in Baaya-Sila Rock Placing and Underwater Excavation','China Harbour Engineering Co.','18 December 2005 - 08 February 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of a temporary loading jetty; 11,000-m3 dredging of existing material at the Revetment; placing 4,800m3 rock toe and 11,000m3 rock armour at Revetment; placing 1,100m3 rock hearting, 1,900m3 rock toe and 8,000m3 rock armour at the Breakwater and placing 11,000 m3 crushed rock & rock hearting at the Quay Wall.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 04:43:41.727000','2025-06-06 08:18:17.803000','2025-06-06 08:18:17.861000',8,3,'en'),(233,'h0rea80idml4afpr1f9zkjoq',' Fujairah F2 Power Plant Offshore Civil Works','Fujairah F2 Power Plant Offshore Civil Works','Alstom Switzerland Ltd','01 January 2008 - 30 September 2009','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of 3 x 4m diameter GRP intake pipes each 500m long completed with 300mm diameter GRP chlorination dosing pipe and RC intake riser; construction of sloping seawall 1km long and construction of a mass concrete outfall structure.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:51:25.229000','2025-06-06 08:18:29.228000','2025-06-06 08:18:29.270000',8,3,'en'),(234,'uvto1o4ayxk8o4m8bo05yy4f',' Rehabilitation of Sewer Sea Outfalls for Colombo Municipal Council (Contract No.GCWMP/ADB/OF01/ICB/Works/01/2012)','Rehabilitation of Sewer Sea Outfalls for Colombo Municipal Council','Ministry of Local Government and Provincial Councils, Colombo Municipal Council','22 May 2013 - 19 May 2015','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes the design and rehabilitation of Mutwal and Wellawatta outfalls.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major works for Mutwal Outfall includes removal of 564m long section of broken concrete pipes and diffusers and replace with new DN2500 HDPE outfall pipe; design and construct a 197m long outfall diffuser section; rehabilitation of the land based junction box and construct a RC access chamber; cleaning and inspection for the completed pipeline.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major works for Wellawatta Outfall includes the cleaning and inspection of the completed pipeline; design and construct a reinforced concrete access chamber and repair pipe damage near theWellawatta Pump Station.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:58:59.155000','2025-06-06 08:19:07.082000','2025-06-06 08:19:07.135000',8,3,'en'),(235,'gmjtohgrj1fczrkng21vydoj',' Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan (Contract No. ST 97/03)','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:48:59.655000','2025-06-06 08:19:20.910000','2025-06-06 08:19:20.994000',8,3,'en'),(236,'xl805j9a0iimf17mpw0m25ms',' Taweelah Power and Water Plant New \"B\" Extension Construction of Seawater Intake','Taweelah Power and Water Plant New \"B\" Extension Construction of Seawater Intake','Taweelah Asia Power Company/Fisia Italimpianti/Arabian Construction Company (ACC)','29 May 2006 - 05 September 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved the installation of 3 seawater intake pipes including the design of concrete anchor blocks, for the Power and Desalination Plant\'s New \'B\' Extension in Taweelah, UAE. Since the construction had to be carried out in the existing basin of the desalination plant, maintaining the water quality of the basin was a major concern. To prevent the pollution of the nearby water in the basin, a double-layer silt curtain was designed and installed to enclose the works area. To further minimize the disturbance to the existing basin, it was proposed to precast the concrete anchor blocks on site. By making use of the buoyancy force, they were lifted and installed underwater by a 500-ton mobile hydraulic crane sitting on temporary steel H-piles driven near the edge of the temporary cut slope. Subsequent intake pipes were installed underwater by divers. The double layer silt curtain proved to be very effective in preventing the deterioration of water quality during the course of construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 04:05:12.856000','2025-06-06 08:19:32.489000','2025-06-06 08:19:32.543000',8,3,'en'),(237,'yph4eweioav91vr48mox95nh',' Terminal 5 Strengthening Works (Kwai Chung Container Port Terminal 1, 2 & 5 Upgrading Works Contract No.2)','Terminal 5 Strengthening Works','Modern Terminal Limited','15 February 2006 - 11 November 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Modern Terminals Limited (MLT) owns and operates Container Terminals 1, 2, 5 and 9 (South) in Kwai Chung Port, Hong Kong, with an annual handling capacity of 5.5 million TEUs. MTL decided to upgrade the capacity her existing container terminals in anticipation of the increasing demand of logistics industry.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Terminal 5 Strengthening project is the first step of structural enhancement in MTL\'s overall upgrading plan. The minimization of interference to the terminal operation from the construction works was of the utmost concern. To maintain 24-hour non-interrupted terminal operation, the works had to be carried out in the bay area progressively under restricted access and hours.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"To enhance the berthing capacity of the terminal, a 350m long insitu retaining wall was proposed at the back-reach of the existing quay deck area. In order to meet the tight schedule, the retaining wall was precast into 4.85m long units weighing approx 100t each and directly installed by lifting pontoons.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Through our highlyqualified team\'s professionalism and proactive attitude, the project was completed two months earlier than schedule.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 04:18:03.323000','2025-06-06 08:19:45.910000','2025-06-06 08:19:45.970000',8,3,'en'),(238,'hfxqgoatvou3z7rgf48roqbr',' Three Runway System Project Contract 3202 – Deep Cement Mixing Works (Package 2)','Three Runway System Project Contract 3202 – Deep Cement Mixing Works (Package 2)','Hong Kong Airport Authority','01 August 2016 - 21 November 2019','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The objective of the DCM works under this Contract is to use the DCM ground improvement method for in-situ stabilization and strengthening of the dumped soil in the East Sha Chau contaminated mud pits within the footprint of the new reclamation, and of the marine sediments under the proposed new third runway and the associated seawalls, without causing deterioration in marine water quality during the course of the works. The volume of sediments to be treated under this Contract is 4.2 m3.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major challenge of this project is to successfully and timely execute and complete the works while maintaining high standard of management of various aspects, particularly environmental concerns and airport height restrictions. Six DCM barges for the works were fabricated and modified in Korea to meet the tight schedule of this Contract.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:30:00.204000','2025-06-06 08:19:58.921000','2025-06-06 08:19:59.140000',8,3,'en'),(239,'uar1s6syc8qnla2u0qv7wiqy',' Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains (Contract No. CV/94/06)','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Port Works Division / Civil Engineering Department','01 September 1995 - 31 January 2000','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes the construction of 450m long vertical seawall, 1000m long sloping rubble seawall, 625m long 4-cells drainage culvert, roads, sewers, drains and watermains and reclamation of 28 hectares of land.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 06:00:41.492000','2025-06-06 08:20:09.880000','2025-06-06 08:20:09.932000',8,3,'en'),(240,'bp5u6ncod6z12l039nzd7le5','Construction of Lung Kwu Chau Jetty (Contract No. CV/2002/11)','Construction of Lung Kwu Chau Jetty','Civil Engineering Department','04 April 2003 - 20 November 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of a precast concrete blockwork jetty (10m by 20m) with a single berth; construction of a concrete catwalk (approximately 22m long); dredging of an approach channel up to 2.5m deep in front of the berth; extension of the existing footpath connecting to the proposed jetty; supply and installation / construction of the associated marine facilities and demolition of the existing jetty upon completion of the proposed jetty.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:50:40.518000','2025-06-06 08:20:21.490000','2025-06-06 08:20:21.546000',8,3,'en'),(241,'r4wkz1s94bqi1uhcx0y1dvu3','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Civil Engineering and Development Department','29 July 2016 - 28 September 2023','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel (TKO-LTT) is intended to address growing external traffic demands from Tseung Kwan O\'s ongoing development. Together with the proposed Trunk Road T2 and Central Kowloon Route, the TKO-LTT will form the express Route 6 network linking West Kowloon and Tseung Kwan O.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project is part of the TKO-LTT which includes constructing an 800m dual two-lane highway (Road P2), with around 600m in the form of a depressed carriageway, 200m of which will be covered by a landscape deck. Associated building, civil, structural, marine, electrical, mechanical, landscaping, environmental protection, and mitigation works are also included.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 02:41:16.463000','2025-06-06 08:20:32.043000','2025-06-06 08:20:32.095000',8,3,'en'),(242,'mdprqccz163e6sls845qwfjh','Demolition and reclamation works for AI Raha Beach Hotel Extension','Demolition and reclamation works for AI Raha Beach Hotel Extension','International Capital Trading L.L.C.