the project.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:51:57.827000','2025-06-06 08:22:21.564000','2025-06-06 08:22:21.623000',8,3,'en'),(250,'zt5iq78cj30grbu3lqcwdxji','Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay (Contract No. CV/98/14)','Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay','Civil Engineering Department','02 August 1999 - 31 December 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes setting up and management of a Public Filling Barging Point at Quarry Bay and carrying out environmental monitoring and implementation of environmental mitigation measures.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:53:58.786000','2025-06-06 08:22:33.697000','2025-06-06 08:22:33.756000',8,3,'en'),(251,'sebrngz255j42ad9itm2qhlk','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo (Contract No. CV/98/15)','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo','Civil Engineering Department','30 July 1999 - 31 December 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the setting up and management of a Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun; carrying out of environmental monitoring and implementation of environmental mitigation measures for Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun; landscape works within Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and management of a Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:55:01.852000','2025-06-06 08:22:45.309000','2025-06-06 08:22:45.370000',8,3,'en'),(252,'t3mk016ovj36cs22gvo4kmy7','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Quarry Bay and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo (Contract No. CV/2001/02)','Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun and Quarry Bay and Public Fill Stockpiling Area at Mui Wo','Civil Engineering Department','05 December 2001 - 07 July 2005','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the modification and management of the Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun & Quarry Bay; management of the Public Filling storage area at Mui Wo and landscaping works within the Public Filling Barging Point at Sai Ying Pun.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:51:47.754000','2025-06-06 08:22:56.427000','2025-06-06 08:22:56.488000',8,3,'en'),(253,'y5knm2adunrwcbyf4rl0s3d6','Reconstruction of Pak Sha Wan Public Pier in Sai Kung and Reconstruction of Dolphins in Shau Kei Wan Typhoon Shelter (Contract No. CV/99/13)','Reconstruction of Pak Sha Wan Public Pier in Sai Kung and Reconstruction of Dolphins in Shau Kei Wan Typhoon Shelter','Civil Engineering Department','01 February 2000 - 31 January 2002','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project is to construct a new public pier in Pak Sha Wan of Sai Kung and to demolish the existing public pier after commissioning of the new public pier.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major challenge of the project is the piling work for the pier deck structure. To overcome problems associated with complex sub-soil condition and to minimize impact to an environmental sensitive area, pre-bored socketted H-pile with permanent steel casing was used to replace the conventional driven pile system. The alternative piling system was successfully completed within the given time frame while substantially reducing impact to the surrounding environment.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Another special feature of the project is to maintain operation of the public pier during construction of the new pier and  demolition of the existing pier. Construction method and sequence were carefully planned to minimize nuisance to public. This includes the provision of temporary covered walkway for pier users, pre-fabrication of the pier and superstructure elements off-site as far as possible to shorten on-site construction time, and demolition of the existing pier by saw cutting method to minimize environmental impacts.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Site was awarded a \\\"Considerate Contractor Site Award\\\" by the Public Works Bureau in consideration of good site management, being considerate to nearby residents and passerbys, environmental consciousness, safety consciousness and law abiding.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:52:49.826000','2025-06-06 08:23:07.692000','2025-06-06 08:23:07.756000',8,3,'en'),(254,'rg16m7412d1vcph469ql7ddt','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A (Contract No. TP37/03)','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads & bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:36:36.838000','2025-06-06 08:23:17.611000','2025-06-06 08:23:17.672000',8,3,'en'),(255,'iyzlq59nougs5ubraqh8kl2r','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun (TMTL 393)','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works. \", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 05:59:32.879000','2025-06-06 08:23:38.022000','2025-06-06 08:23:38.129000',8,3,'en'),(256,'mihwqi6s5gjpfyfzdowpfs73','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment (CRPC South East Tsing Yi Oil Terminal Contract No. 3)','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment','China Resources Petroleum (Group) Company Limited','01 November 1993 - 01 July 1995','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project was the major civil work for the installation of the China Resources Petrochem Oil Terminal at Tsing Yi Island. The project involved the construction of a new tanker pier for 80,000 dwt fuel tankers, reclamation of 7 hectares of land by 2.8M cu.m of marine fill with substantial and stringent ground improvement works, dredging for reclamation and fairway realignment.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:46:06.165000','2025-06-06 08:24:08.943000','2025-06-06 08:24:09.009000',8,3,'en'),(257,'h5zfqnwarn9khb9go6l5sq05','Stanley Area Sewerage and Sewage Disposal Submarine Outfall (Contract No. CV/89/32)','Stanley Area Sewerage and Sewage Disposal Submarine Outfall','Drainage Services Department','01 February 1991 - 31 July 1992','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes the construction of a 610m diameter, 2.3km long submarine outfall pipeline to a point in Sheung Sze Mun; construction of a 610mm diameter, 210m long overflow pipeline parallel to the outfall; construction of a valve chamber and installation of a cathodic protection system.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 08:51:01.112000','2025-06-06 08:24:20.404000','2025-06-06 08:24:20.461000',8,3,'en'),(259,'r28r71bi0hp67d12v86mdtx0','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (Contract No: HK/2009/01)','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 December 2009 - 31 May 2016','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The group was awarded one of the contracts in Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works mainly include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass (CWB) tunnel at the water channel between the two phases of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (HKCEC) and other associated works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-01 03:24:12.974000','2025-06-06 08:24:46.281000','2025-06-06 08:24:46.393000',8,3,'en'),(260,'nq1b8njg0pb7lb4x4vbnv1qb',' 阿聯酋鋼鐵製造廠鋼鐵整合工程','阿聯酋鋼鐵製造廠鋼鐵整合工程','General Holding Corporation (GHC)','2007 年 07 月 03 日 